The more limited scope of the temporary cease and desist order is not problematic to the Department because the authority
provides the SEC with the ability to issue such an order not only if a rule violation has occurred but also if one is threatened.
Since the SEC is the appropriate regulatory agency for government securities brokers or dealers subject to  402.2,
an impending violation of a  402.2 requirement would be cause for the issuance of a temporary cease and desist
order. The SEC would still be able to anticipate sizeable capital withdrawals that might result in violations of  402.2,
since it would receive the notifications required by the proposed rule, as described earlier. The SEC would only be
